{"type":"text","timestamp":1781082487176,"sessionID":"ses_14f37e5c0ffewUVDEfJ2NQ59Gq","part":{"id":"prt_eb0c9ede4001NbPCyJ1NNQDdHx","messageID":"msg_eb0c9e524001Z7QNL5tMf9Bp6F","sessionID":"ses_14f37e5c0ffewUVDEfJ2NQ59Gq","type":"text","text":"No prior fairness.json — good, ignoring others per instructions. Let me check key fairness aspects:\n\n1. Instruction says agent must support `-l` for cases that use it (acknowledged).\n2. The `--show-control-chars` is mentioned in instruction. \n3. Default quoting behavior — instruction notes default is `shell-escape` \"when output is not a terminal in recent coreutils\" but the test environment pins behavior via flags. Yet there is a test `t6_special_names_default` which uses NO flags! Let me look at this carefully:","time":{"start":1781082484196,"end":1781082487168}}}
